headline: Marine Le Pen returns to court for appeal of graft conviction
description: The French far right's leader, sentenced in 2025 to four years in prison and a five-year ban on holding an elected office after being convicted of embezzlement of pubic funds, goes back to court with 11 co-defendants for a one-month trial starting Tuesday.

headline: Venezuela's Delcy Rodriguez faces an obstacle-strewn path
'The Islamic Republic of Iran is entering its final phase'
Ex-Fed chiefs, lawmakers slam US probe into Jerome Powell
description: Powell said the Fed received grand jury subpoenas and threats of a criminal indictment relating to Senate testimony he gave in June. Ex-Fed chiefs Ben Bernanke, Alan Greenspan and Janet Yellen slammed the DOJ's probe, calling it 'an unprecedented attempt to use prosecutorial attacks' to undermine the Fed's independence.

headline: Paris FC's Ikoné stuns PSG, knocks out former club from French Cup
description: Paris FC beat their city rivals 1-0 to reach the last 16 of the French Cup. Paris Saint-Germain lost their first home game in the competition since 2022 and suffered their first last-32 defeat since 2014.

headline: In Los Angeles, the specter of lingering pollution after major wildfires
description: The fires that occurred a year ago released toxic smoke that seeped into homes that were either untouched or only partially damaged. A French researcher based in California has demonstrated that these fumes contain extremely high levels of dangerous heavy metals.

headline: Paris launches project for Montparnasse renovation
description: The architect Renzo Piano unveiled his new renovation plan for the shopping center. Construction is hoped to start in 2028.

description: Once a month at London's The Posh Club, burlesque acts and striptease in a nightclub atmosphere delight Brits over 60, who let loose until late in the afternoon.

headline: The Ukrainian-held Donbas, a land of ruins and grief
description: This region in eastern Ukraine now has only 200,000 inhabitants, compared to five million before the Russian invasion of 2022. Le Monde visited the area still under Kyiv's authority.

headline: 'Don't forget you saved my life': Letter to the stranger who gave me their bone marrow
description: Hélène Schlesinger was 37 and had a husband, two children, and plenty of plans for the future when she learned, in 2022, that she had leukemia. For months, the young woman fought as she waited for a bone marrow transplant. She lives thanks to an anonymous donor. All she knows is that he is German and that a part of him now lives inside her.
